Facts (layer 2):

`x :: Number` (ConstantDefinition):
  has definition constraints
  has type `Number` or `String`
  is a definition

`Number` (NamedType):
  has type `Number` or `String`
  is a type
  resolved to 1 definition(s): `Number : type`

`x : "42"` (AssignmentStatement):
  has type `()`

`"42"` (StringExpression):
  has type `Number` or `String`
  is an expression



Feedback:

`x :: Number` (conflicting-types)

  `x :: Number` is a `Number` or a `String`, but it can only be one of these.
  
  `x :: Number` must be the same type as `"42"` and `Number`; double-check these.
  
  -  `"42"` is a `String`.


`Number` (conflicting-types)

  `Number` is a `Number` or a `String`, but it can only be one of these.
  
  `Number` must be the same type as `"42"` and `x :: Number`; double-check these.
  
  -  `"42"` is a `String`.


`"42"` (conflicting-types)

  `"42"` is a `Number` or a `String`, but it can only be one of these.
  
  `"42"` must be the same type as `Number` and `x :: Number`; double-check these.
  
  -  `"42"` is a `String`.


